<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,1805,1938]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1805,1830]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Discussion.</emphasis>
Apart from the lighter coloration, the specimen at hand is similar to 
<emphasis box="[1100,1290,1805,1829]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
C. p. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Haan" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[1161,1290,1805,1829]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllacrididae" genus="Caustogryllacris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="podocausta">podocausta</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. The teeth at the bottom of the apical swellings of the male ninth abdominal tergite are compressed and with acute tip while in the specimen from Gunung Arjuna described above these teeth are rounded and with slightly blunt tip. The subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Haan" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[308,469,1913,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllacrididae" genus="Caustogryllacris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="podocausta">
<emphasis box="[308,469,1913,1937]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">C. podocausta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are in need of a revision, including a severe re-examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[1219,1281,1914,1938]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">types</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
